very
little
of
his
time
there
in
the
future.
He
has
many
friends,
and
is
at
a
time
of
life
when
friends
and
engagements
are
continually
increasing."
"If
he
means
to
be
but
little
at
Netherfield,
it
would
be
better
for
the
neighbourhood
that
he
should
give
up
the
place
entirely,
for
then
we
might
possibly
get
a
settled
family
there.
But,
perhaps,
Mr.
Bingley
did
not
