"I
should
not
be
surprised,"
said
Darcy,
"if
he
were
to
give
it
up
as
soon
as
any
eligible
purchase
offers."
Elizabeth
made
no
answer.
She
was
afraid
of
talking
longer
of
his
friend;
and,
having
nothing
else
to
say,
was
now
determined
to
leave
the
trouble
of
finding
a
subject
to
him.
He
took
the
